DISTELL Africa has announced the launch of a new brand of non-alcoholic wine, 4th Street, to cater to the needs of Nigerian consumers. Speaking at the unveiling, the Managing Director, Distell Nigeria, Steve Ighorimoto, said, “4th Street has been a trailblazer in the sweet wine category and has grown significantly over the years in Nigeria. “Following the success of local production of our wine, I am excited to share the launch of the first 4th street non-alcoholic sparkling wine, a first for the 4th Street brand across the entire Distell business. “The focus of the launch campaign is to position 4th Street’s new non-alcoholic sparkling wine as the drink of choice for young, upbeat, urban, and social Nigerians looking to celebrate. Looking at the ATL activities, we will be driving the new product on all digital platforms with linked promotions. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com